                </div>
                <h3 style={{fontFamily:'Fraunces,serif',fontSize:'clamp(26px,3.5vw,38px)',fontWeight:700,color:'#F5F0E8',lineHeight:1.1,marginBottom:16}}>Holiday<br/>In EMI</h3>
                <p style={{fontSize:14,lineHeight:1.75,color:'rgba(245,240,232,.55)',maxWidth:340,marginBottom:28}}>Your loan disburses on a Tuesday. You shouldn&apos;t have to pay EMI by next month. With EMI Holiday, your first payment starts 3–6 months later — giving you time to actually use the money.</p>
                <div style={{display:'flex',gap:0,border:'1px solid rgba(201,168,76,.15)',borderRadius:12,overflow:'hidden',marginBottom:28,maxWidth:280}}>
                  <div style={{flex:1,padding:'14px 16px',borderRight:'1px solid rgba(201,168,76,.1)'}}>
                    <div className="stat-num" style={{fontSize:22,fontWeight:700,color:'#C9A84C'}}>3–6</div>
                    <div style={{fontSize:10,color:'rgba(245,240,232,.35)',marginTop:2}}>Months free</div>
                  </div>
